Hi Rees.  I think we can only speculate at this point.  With all the references to air, it makes 
me assume that an &#39;air person&#39; could be the &#39;humans&#39; (as has also been referenced) who 
are using their &#39;air portals&#39; - thereby making us &#39;air people&#39; ... not necessarily that we 
breath air, which could be the case as well, but I&#39;m sort of leaning toward this term being a 
reference of communication.  

If we &quot;enter their air&quot; through &quot;air portals&quot; and they &quot;give us air&quot; for communication, I think 
that makes us &quot;air people&quot; in their frame of reference.  But really, that&#39;s just a guess.  

Margaret

